{
  "text": "One of these is the reversal of myelin differentiation. Genes coding for the key myelin transcription factor Egr2 (Krox20), the enzymes of cholesterol synthesis, structural proteins such as P0, myelin basic protein (MBP), and membrane associated proteins like myelin associated glycoprotein (MAG) and periaxin are all rapidly down-regulated (reviewed in [CITATION_1] . Conversely molecules that characterize pre-myelinating Schwann cells in developing nerves (immature Schwann cells), including L1, neural cell adhesion molecule (NCAM), p75 neurotrophin receptor (p75NTR) and glial fibrillary acidic protein (GFAP), are up-regulated [CITATION_2] .",
